&#x200B;

My roommate eventually came back and I told them about the situation. I suggested we let C a week to decide his next step and then we'd ask him to move out. This might sound short but come on, the guy is 38, married with a kid, he should think about his actions. My flatmates agreed and I let M & C know about our decision.

&#x200B;

The week went by and C locked himself in M's room every night. So I eventually knocked on the door. M opened and C was laying on the bed (clothed), I told him that the week was over and we were expecting him to move out. C rolled over on the bed and didn't say a word. M went up to me half crying and told me to that she was allowed to spend time with her BF. I then said to both of them that staying home doing nothing wouldn't help anyone and that we still expected him to move out. Then I left.

&#x200B;

He left the day after and now I'm treated like the A here. AITA ?

